Stencil in the dark;
Banksy laughs behind the paint.
Power framed in jest.

Keith Haring’s bold lines,
march for love, rage, hope, and truth;
walls still speak his name.

Jeff Koons and his team,
shape wonder in mirrored steel;
joy made luminous.

Joseph Kosuth speaks;
art is thought, not decoration,
questions shape the form.

In David Salle’s name;
images forget themselves,
echo over edge.
